    content: [
      { heading: "What referral marketing is", body: "Referral marketing is the structured practice of encouraging existing customers to recommend your business to their network, typically in exchange for an incentive for both the referrer and the new customer. It turns word-of-mouth that happens organically into a measurable, scalable acquisition channel. A well-designed referral programme is often the highest-quality, lowest-CAC channel available." },
      { heading: "Why referred customers are better", body: "Referred customers consistently outperform non-referred customers on every quality metric. They convert at higher rates (pre-sold by a trusted peer). They churn at lower rates. They have higher LTV. They refer more customers themselves. Referred customers are simply better customers." },
      { heading: "Programme mechanics", body: "A typical refer-a-friend programme gives the referrer a reward (discount, store credit, cash) when someone they invited makes their first purchase, and gives the new customer a welcome incentive. The reward needs to be large enough to motivate action but not so large that it attracts incentive-seekers who refer friends not genuinely interested in the product." },
      { heading: "The viral coefficient", body: "The viral coefficient (K-factor) measures the number of new customers each existing customer generates through referrals. K = (referral rate) x (conversion rate). A K above 1.0 means each customer generates more than one new customer — the product is genuinely viral. Even a K of 0.2 means referrals are generating 20% of new customers essentially for free." },
      { heading: "Tools and timing", body: "Referral programme software (ReferralCandy, Yotpo Loyalty, Mention Me) integrates with eCommerce platforms and automates tracking, rewarding, and communication. The timing of the referral ask matters enormously: the best moment is immediately after the customer's first delightful experience — post first delivery when NPS is highest." },
    ],
    relatedSlugs: ["what-is-influencer-marketing-roi", "what-is-customer-acquisition-cost-marketing", "what-is-social-commerce"],
