    keywords: ["daily revenue tracking", "POS revenue report", "daily sales report", "retail revenue tracking", "daily takings POS", "POS sales dashboard", "track daily sales"],
    keyTakeaways: [
      "AskBiz POS shows live daily revenue from the moment you process the first sale of the day.",
      "Revenue is broken down by payment method, staff member, and product category.",
      "Comparing today's performance to the same day last week helps you spot trends early.",
    ],
    content: [
      { heading: "Why daily revenue visibility matters", body: "In traditional retail, many shop owners do not know their actual daily revenue until the till is counted at close of business. That is twelve hours of trading in the dark. With AskBiz POS, revenue updates in real time after every transaction. By mid-morning, you know whether today is tracking ahead or behind your average. By lunchtime, you have enough data to make decisions: should you run an afternoon promotion? Pull a slow-moving product from the front display? Adjust staffing for the rest of the shift? This kind of intra-day visibility used to be reserved for chain retailers with expensive analytics platforms. AskBiz puts it on your phone. The daily revenue screen sits one tap away from the selling interface, so checking your numbers takes seconds, not minutes." },
      { heading: "What the daily revenue screen shows", body: "The daily revenue screen in AskBiz POS shows a running total of all sales processed today, split by payment method (cash, card, or mixed). Below the total, you see a breakdown by product category — so you can see at a glance that hot drinks are outselling cold drinks two-to-one, or that accessories are having a slow day. There is also a breakdown by staff member, which is invaluable if you have multiple people on the till. The screen includes a comparison to the same day last week and the same day last month. If today is a Tuesday, you see last Tuesday's revenue alongside today's figure, giving you immediate context. A green arrow means you are ahead; a red arrow means you are behind. At the bottom, AskBiz shows the average transaction value and the total number of transactions, which helps you distinguish between a few big sales and many small ones." },
      { heading: "Using daily data to make better decisions", body: "The real power of daily revenue tracking is not just knowing the number — it is acting on it. Here are practical examples. If your revenue at 11am is 40% below the same time last week, something has changed. Is footfall down? Has a competitor opened nearby? Is the weather keeping people indoors? You can investigate and respond. If your card-to-cash ratio has shifted dramatically, you might have a card terminal issue worth checking. If one staff member consistently generates higher average transaction values, you can learn what they are doing differently and train others to do the same. AskBiz surfaces these patterns automatically through its analytics engine, but even a quick glance at the daily revenue screen will tell you more about your business health than waiting until month-end to review your bank statements." },
      { heading: "End-of-day summary and reporting", body: "At the end of the trading day — or whenever you decide to close the till — AskBiz generates a comprehensive end-of-day summary. This includes total revenue, transaction count, average transaction value, payment method split, revenue by category, revenue by staff member, refunds processed, and discounts given. You can view this summary on screen, email it to yourself, or export it as a CSV for your accountant. If you manage the cash in your till, AskBiz can compare the expected cash amount (based on cash transactions processed) with your counted amount to identify any discrepancies. This cash-up process takes minutes rather than the half-hour many retailers spend manually tallying receipts against till contents. Over time, the daily summaries feed into weekly and monthly trend reports, giving you an increasingly clear picture of your business trajectory." },
    ],
    relatedSlugs: ["pos-multi-staff-performance", "pos-30-day-export", "pos-vat-calculations", "pos-inventory-management"],
