    content: [
      { heading: "From till to dashboard in real time", body: "Every sale processed through AskBiz POS is recorded in your central data store immediately. Within seconds, that transaction updates your dashboard: total revenue ticks upward, the product leaderboard reshuffles, and the daily sales counter increments. There is no batch import, no overnight sync, and no manual export. This is the fundamental difference between a standalone till and an integrated POS — your intelligence layer sees every transaction the moment it happens. For a shop owner, this means you can check your phone at lunchtime and know exactly how the morning went, which products moved, and whether you are on track to hit your daily target." },
      { heading: "Key POS widgets for your dashboard", body: "AskBiz automatically makes several POS-specific widgets available when the module is active. **Revenue Today** shows a running total with a comparison to the same day last week. **Units Sold** tracks volume separately from value — useful for spotting whether a revenue increase comes from selling more items or more expensive items. **Average Basket Size** calculates the mean transaction value across all sales today. **Top Products** ranks your best sellers by revenue or volume over any period you choose. **Sales by Staff Member** shows which cashiers are processing the most transactions — useful for shift planning and performance reviews. You can pin any of these to your default home dashboard so they load first every morning." },
      { heading: "Combining POS with online sales", body: "If you also sell through Shopify, Amazon, Etsy, or another connected platform, AskBiz merges your POS data with online data into a single view. This is where the real intelligence emerges. You can see that a product sells well online but barely moves in-store, or that weekday in-store revenue outperforms weekends while the reverse is true online. The **Multi-Channel Revenue** widget shows all channels side by side. The **Product Performance** view lets you compare the same SKU across channels. This omnichannel visibility is something that typically costs enterprise retailers thousands of pounds in bespoke analytics — AskBiz delivers it automatically because the POS is built in rather than bolted on." },
      { heading: "Setting up your POS dashboard", body: "Head to **Dashboards → Create Dashboard** and select the POS template, or build one from scratch by adding widgets from the POS category. Arrange them in the order that matches your daily review — most owners put revenue and units sold at the top left, product performance below, and staff metrics on the right. Save it as your default view so it loads automatically when you open AskBiz. If you share the dashboard with a store manager, they see the same real-time data without needing access to the full AskBiz admin. Dashboard sharing respects role permissions, so a manager sees sales data but not billing or account settings." },
    ],
    relatedSlugs: ["pos-daily-revenue-tracking", "pos-multi-staff-performance", "askbiz-pos-overview", "pos-ai-chat-questions"],
